<br>
I loged in shadowind in EC and was looking for spells for my guild that i was in, when i see someone auc WTB com. Now vailon has one of these from when we all fought in keal. Now to shead light on the not getting back to him part... I had scrolled up to read the rest of the auctions and that is why there was a delay in me getting back to him. He got realy pissed that i didnt get back to him right away with a price on the cloak. So this starts off the bad feelings. When I finaly see his message I reply with &quot;make an offer&quot; (hell i dont spend much time in EC and no idea what its worth) His reply (bare with me long time ago) was something like no i dont wana buy from you becuase i hear your the one that stole it. (somewhere along the convernsation i hear that someone lost a com in wc. Well folks shadowind was loged in EC and i hadnt played Eq at all all day. So i log in to be accused of theift. Im sure many of you would have handled this better then i did. I dont recall everything that i said to him but after he told me some pretty nasty stuff i replyed back in kind with some bad words of my own.  Now frustrated i loged on my cleric to continue my day, but wait the thought enters my mind that yet another bad story is out about shadowind. ( BTW Shadowind never stole, cheated, or betrayed anyone ever, ok he argured and basicly didnt get along with many people and as such no one will forgive or forget to my great sarrow. So Shadowind has been retired never to play again untill the day people can look past the rumors and give him a second chance. <br>
